    "method": "chemical synthesis",
    "description": "Produced by neutralizing citric acid with calcium hydroxide or calcium carbonate. The degree of neutralization and reaction conditions determine which form is produced: monocalcium citrate (E333i), dicalcium citrate (E333ii), or tricalcium citrate (E333iii). Tricalcium citrate is the most commonly used form in food applications."
